\DOC BEGIN_STACK

\TYPE {BEGIN_STACK : (string -> term -> term list -> thm list -> void)}

\SYNOPSIS
Create a window stack.

\LIBRARY window

\DESCRIBE
{BEGIN_STACK `name` "r f" hyps thms} creates a new window stack containing
a single window with:
focus {"f"}, relation {"r"}, hypotheses {hyps}, relevant theorems {thms} and
suppositions {[]}.
The new stack has the name {`name`} and is made the current stack.

\FAILURE
{BEGIN_STACK `name` "r f" hyps thms} fails if there already exists
a window stack called {`name`}.

\USES
Use this command to start an interactive reasoning session.

\SEEALSO
create_win, END_STACK, SET_STACK, ALL_STACKS, CURRENT_NAME

\ENDDOC
